UNIVERSITY MISSION, GOALS, ADVANTAGES
- Mission: To prepare ethically responsible leaders who are committed to the development of democratic and prosperous societies in Central Asia.
- Goals: Deliver high-quality education based on the American liberal arts model, promote critical thinking, and support academic freedom.
- Advantages: Double degrees with foreign partner universities, international faculty, small class sizes, practical clinics, modern campus facilities, and intensive language programs in English and Chinese.

ORGANIZATIONAL STRUCTURE
- President: Dr. Kamila Duishebaevna Sharshekeeva
- Board of Trustees: Consists of international educational leaders and local community stakeholders who oversee the university's development.
- Academic Departments: Managed by program coordinators and deans responsible for curriculum quality.

RESEARCH ACTIVITY
- Business Clinic: Active since September 2016. Located under the Department of Business Administration. Provides consulting and advising services for local entrepreneurs, led by senior students under faculty guidance.
- Legal Clinic: Provides free legal consultations and advice to Tokmok community members, run by senior Law students under supervision of qualified faculty lawyers. Helps students develop practical legal skills.

FOUNDER BIO
- Yang Chia Shan (Elder Yang / Captain Yang): A philanthropist and Christian educational leader who co-founded IUCA in 2008. Through his organizations CASA (Central Asia Sharing Aid) and the Yrayym Foundation, he funded the university's construction and scholarship programs to support underprivileged students in Tokmok and Central Asia.
- Dr. Kamila Sharshekeeva: Instrumental co-founder and president, formerly Minister of Education of Kyrgyzstan and Provost of AUCA. Led the academic development and licensing of IUCA programs.

