SCHOLARSHIPS AND FINANCIAL AID
- Full Scholarship: Offered to students who score 200 or above on the ORT (Kyrgyzstan National Main Test). This covers 100% of the tuition fee.
- Partial Financial Aid: Available for students from low-income, large, or single-parent families, orphans, and students showing excellent academic progress (GPA 3.5+). Covers 20% to 75% of tuition.
- Merit Discounts: Awarded to top-performing students at the end of each academic year.

ADMISSIONS PROCESS AND REQUIRED DOCUMENTS
- Kyrgyz Republic Citizens:
  - Requirements: ORT certificate (main test score must meet the national threshold, e.g., 110+).
  - Documents: Passport copy, ORT original certificate, 6 photos (3x4 cm), school graduation certificate (Attestat) original, medical certificate (Form 086-U).
- Foreign / International Citizens:
  - Requirements: Pass the university's internal English and general exams.
  - Documents: Passport copy with valid study visa, high school diploma (translated to Russian/Kyrgyz and notarized), 6 photos (3x4 cm), medical certificate (Form 086-U) including HIV test.

